Description: Fragment of floor and ring foot of black-glazed pottery open vase (bowl?); glaze fired dark brown inside. Reserved stand-ring and underside, which has broad black band to the outside and dot and ring central. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 535)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1865)
